<title>BELGIUM: Euro aluminium producers defend import tariff.</title>
<headline>Euro aluminium producers defend import tariff.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-06-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>The European Aluminium Association said on Tuesday that it continued to support a tariff on aluminium imports.</p>
<p>&quot;The association's position is always the same,&quot; Bernard Legrand, EAA chairman, told an annual news conference.</p>
<p>Legrand added that a &quot;large majority&quot; wanted to keep the present tariff structure for wrought and unwrought aluminium imports. A six percent tariff is applied.</p>
<p>In April, the U.S. Aluminum Association asked the U.S. Trade Representative to press for the removal of what it said was a trade-distorting tariff.</p>
<p>EU producers say it provides protection against fluctuations of the dollar -- the currency used for aluminium trade -- and cheap imports from eastern Europe.</p>
<p>--Brussels Bureau +322 287 6830</p>
